This would layer itself seamlessly and transparently back onto the blog owner's blog or any commercial website. Artiklz also enables users to create a central registry on its platform so that the user can go to any blog or website and (a) follow the blog or author(s) of the blog/website and its respective comments on the web, (b) continue to monitor a specific posting of comments and ensuing reply threads to keep the conversation of comments alive, and (c) follow their favorite commenter on the web.  The benefits to the blogger or website owner is clear: (1) the blogger/website retains the continuity of the downstream comments that are generated off of the blogger's/website's IP (content), and (2) other readers of the blog/website get to see what and where else other commenter/comments are coming from without ever having to leave the blog or website.

We work with families of wealth, the operators in their family offices and family enterprises, and their strategic advisors and providers to solve their unique family office and wealth challenges. The families we work with are typically at a crossroad, facing situations that require complex change solutions. We are thought leaders, innovators, educators, and practitioners in the family office industry. By design, we are both independent and unbiased. Our team is highly experienced (having been operators in family offices, roles in family foundations, and on family business boards of directors) and is well positioned to support clients in all areas of the family office. We blend 50+ years of experience working in the family office, wealth management, and professional services industries, with our drive for excellence and our dedication to finding the best solutions.

Full Description: Measurement Analytics, Inc. (MAI) is an intellectual property company that has acquired technology utilization rights from which it has refined and developed innovative and cost effective solutions for automated in-patient blood glucose measurement. These advantages are “Flagged” in our EquityNet Business Plan and illustrate the advantages of applying our business model to very large and rapidly growing markets. Full Description: Commotion Wireless is a free, open-source communication tool that uses wireless devices to create decentralized mesh networks, allowing devices to connect directly to each other without going through a centralized point. Its mesh networks are self-healing and can grow organically, and also allow for easy sharing of services over the network, such as internet and applications. Commotion Wireless provides a way for its users to share their internet connection with the people around them, but it is not a replacement for their internet connection. Its features include creating a simple, easy-to-use communications tool that anyone can set up and use without technical expertise; providing a platform for building community wireless networks and hosting local applications; building a tool for creating infrastructure that is resilient against surveillance and disruption; and developing a flexible, open-source software platform that programmers around the globe can continually adapt and build upon. Commotion Wireless is based in Washington, District of Columbia.
